@admol311079 @Dta60500Tame @NSWHealth Yes PCR would be the high standard no doubt

Better than RAT but that’s all we have at the moment better than nothing I guess

@Fluckit2Fluckit @IanBrad89742422 @NSWHealth While I think party attendees should have been cautious, I wonder if promoters had COVID Safe plans, if NSW govt took steps to ensure COVID safe events. However having dealt with SafeWork NSW at former job I have little faith in regulators, they prefer individual responsibility.

@sidherian @IanBrad89742422 @NSWHealth The after party I attended was mostly outside...I said mostly. Zero distancing and no masks, lots of bare asses too. Surprised no one caught pink eye and stomach flu either. Dress code should have been, wear full underwear that covers your butt cheeks at all times

@ToniEriksson2 @IanBrad89742422 @NSWHealth I think instant gratification is now more important. I’ve heard those around my own age (57), saying partying is vital to mental health. Mental health would be a 💩 load worse if you have to deal with LongCOVID.
@sidherian @IanBrad89742422 @NSWHealth Yes, I have to admit I was surprised. So we never learn?

@ToniEriksson2 @IanBrad89742422 @NSWHealth I’m shocked that our community worked so hard during AIDS crisis & is now blithely partying while another considerably more infectious virus is rolling through & destroying lives. Ignoring ongoing debilitating disease wrought by LongCOVID.

@Fluckit2Fluckit @IanBrad89742422 @NSWHealth It’s after parties that have become mass exposure events. Because how could anyone have known that having hundreds of people crowded into venues for hours might be perfect conditions for virus spread? 
Anyone who’s been paying attention.
@sidherian @IanBrad89742422 @NSWHealth My wife and I thought the same. We watched on tv, had our bunting up at home. We had fun 🏳️‍🌈🏳️‍⚧️
